commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the tag system was used to identify who is in which module, but it has proven to be annying when it
comes to searching because it is difficult to differentiate between modules and tutorials,
as well as which tutorial is connected to which module using it.
This commit adds a new field to Person comprising of module and tutorial objects to remedy the problem.

commitResults.messageTitle: Make minor edits to removeFromTutorial and deleteModule

commitResults.messageBody:
DeveloperGuide was previously using PlantUML tags to display images, but
this was not working on either GitHub preview nor in IDE so images of
the diagrams are saved instead.

DG: Diagrams seemed to not work - the puml files do not update
accordingly, despite attempts to fix it. Thus, images of the puml
diagrams, stored in images are used instead. Any update to the diagrams
thus need to be saved in the images.

Storage new saves the modules & tutorials fields that each person has.
No checking is done to make sure that these modules and tutorials exist.

commitResults.messageBody: Make Storage affect the module/tutorial fields that Person has

Trying to not trip up the reader: Previously,
module.getModuleCode() and tutorial.getModuleName() both obtained module
code. Thus, tutorial.getModuleName() is refactored to getModuleCode to
not confuse future developers.

Retified some incorrect comments that referenced the wrong command, like
DeleteTutorialCommandParser's comment saying it would create a
AddTutorialCommand. Also changed a few GUI messages to better reflect
the command.

No functional code changes.
